<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">English spelling is famously inconsistent — and Scrabble rewards players who embrace its quirks. Silent letters are tiles that score full points despite making no sound. A K in KNIFE still earns 5 points. A W in WRONG still earns 4. Knowing these patterns turns spelling oddities into scoring advantages.</p>

